Enumeration Type Documentation

enum ECOLORTRANSFORM

Purpose: To provide configuration details for the client/server.

File: UTConfig.h Author: Kevin Bray Created: 11-24-07 Copyright © 2004 Bootstrap Studios. All rights reserved. Enumerations supported color transforms. Note that the enums are named as ECT_source_target. Also, the transforms require that the source color format have at least the required components.

Enumerator:
ECT_NONE 
ECT_BGR_YCoCg 
ECT_BGRA_YCoCgA 
ECT_XY_EXY  this is an experimental format that encodes an exponent and 2 6-bit XY values, with 1 bit implied. Format is: E:2, X:s1m5, Y:s1m5. E is implicitly negative and biased by -1, meaning the largest exponent value is -1, with the smallest being -4. The largest absolute value that can be represented by either X or Y is +/-0.984375f, while the smallest absolute value is 0.001953125. If m == 0, and s == 0, then the value is treated as 0. This is not currently supported, but might be in the future if some compression strategies turn out to be a win in this format.
